Nov 4 2004	An English hotel!	The pricey (what isn't in London?), family-run Goring Hotel is a real, once-in-a-lifetime treat. Tucked around the corner from bustling Victoria Station, a few blocks from Eaton Square and ultra-posh Belgravia, and Buckingham Palace, the low-profile hotel is a five-story, late Victorian brick pile with beautiful, clubby public rooms (the lobby's bright yellow!) and its own private garden. Our room was small considering the cost, but the furniture, bath, beds and linens were dreamy. Service is finely tuned and friendly. BUT, you'd think they'd have a continental breakfast service considering the cost. Also, there's a certain, ye-olde traditionalist smugness about the place that gets cloying after five days. I nevertheless recommend it to anyone who can afford it, who doesn't know London very well, wants a posh, small hotel and wants to be well located. God save the Queen!	
